SOUL CERTIFICATION & OFFICIAL NETWORK
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The SaveYourSoul protocol uses HMAC-SHA256 soul certificates
derived from a SOUL_MASTER_KEY. Only the original author controls
the SOUL_MASTER_KEY for the canonical SYS network at:

    https://sys.uxprojects-jok.com

Self-hosted implementations generate their own independent
SOUL_MASTER_KEY and operate as isolated instances — they are
not part of the official SYS network and cannot issue
certificates valid on the canonical network.

Official certification of third-party implementations as
"SaveYourSoul Compatible" is at the sole discretion of
Jan-Oliver Karo — UX-Projects.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SOUL REGISTRY (BLOCKCHAIN)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The SoulRegistry smart contract (contracts/SoulRegistry.sol),
when deployed by the copyright holder on Polygon mainnet,
creates an immutable on-chain record of authorship and the
canonical soul registration. Third-party deployments of this
contract create independent registries and are not affiliated
with or endorsed by the canonical SaveYourSoul registry.

